<paragraph id="162C1D29FFADFF93FF04FA4DE0C1F96B" blockId="6.[151,1437,1436,1751]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName id="D19366AAFFADFF93FF04FA4DE004FA52" authorityName="Maskell" authorityYear="1879" box="[151,325,1436,1462]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patella">
<emphasis id="24E7C13BFFADFF93FF04FA4DE004FA52" box="[151,325,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Inglisia patella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from 
<collectingCountry id="6E845DB9FFADFF93FDADFA4CE398FA52" box="[574,729,1436,1463]" name="New Zealand" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
, and was redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation id="720260D8FFADFF93FB92FA4DE420FA53" author="Hodgson, C. J. &amp; Henderson, R. C." box="[1025,1377,1436,1463]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" refId="ref11515" refString="Hodgson, C. J. &amp; Henderson, R. C. (2000) Coccidae (Insecta: Hemiptera: Coccoidea). Manaaki Whenua Press, Lincoln, Canterbury, 259 pp." type="book" year="2000">Hodgson &amp; Henderson (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. It is unlike any other known soft scale and it is clear that none of the other seven species currently included in the genus are congeneric with it. Here the three African species, 
<taxonomicName id="D19366AAFFADFF93FC97FA34E54BFA1B" authority="Hall, 1935" authorityName="Hall" authorityYear="1935" box="[772,1034,1508,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grevilliae">
<emphasis id="24E7C13BFFADFF93FC97FA34E2C6FA1A" box="[772,903,1508,1534]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">I. grevilliae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="720260D8FFADFF93FC03FA35E54BFA1B" author="Hall, W. J." box="[912,1034,1508,1535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" pagination="73 - 84" refId="ref11180" refString="Hall, W. J. (1935) Observations on the Coccidae of southern Rhodesia - VI. Stylops, 4, 73 - 84. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1935. tb 00561. x" type="journal article" year="1935">Hall, 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D19366AAFFADFF93FB84FA34E412FA1A" authority="Hodgson, 1967 b" authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="1969" baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" box="[1047,1363,1508,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pluvialis">
<emphasis id="24E7C13BFFADFF93FB84FA34E5CEFA1A" box="[1047,1167,1508,1534]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">I. pluvialis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="720260D8FFADFF93FB0BFA35E412FA1A" author="Hodgson, C. J." box="[1176,1363,1508,1534]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref11311" refString="Hodgson, C. J. (1967 b) A revision of the species of Inglisia Maskell (Homoptera: Coccoidea) recorded from the Ethiopian region. Arnoldia, Rhodesia, 3 (23), 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1967">Hodgson, 1967b</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D19366AAFFADFF93FA1FFA34E09CF9C7" authority="Newstead, 1917" authorityName="Newstead" authorityYear="1917" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="theobromae">
<emphasis id="24E7C13BFFADFF93FA1FFA34E05DF9C6" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">I. theobromae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="720260D8FFADFF93FEB5F9D9E09CF9C7" author="Newstead, R." box="[294,477,1544,1571]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref11922" refString="Newstead, R. (1917) Observations on scale-insects (Coccidae) - IV. Bulletin of Entomological Research, 8, 1 - 34. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0007485300036476" type="journal article" year="1917">Newstead, 1917</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="D19366AAFFADFF93FD25F9D9E548F9C7" authority="Cockerell, 1900" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1900" box="[694,1033,1544,1571]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Cryptinglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="24E7C13BFFADFF93FD25F9D9E20BF9C6" box="[694,842,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Cryptinglisia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="720260D8FFADFF93FCC7F9D9E548F9C7" author="Cockerell, T. D. A." box="[852,1033,1544,1571]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" pagination="173 - 174" refId="ref10853" refString="Cockerell, T. D. A. (1900) A new genus of Coccidae injuring the roots of the grapevine in South Africa. The Entomologist, 33, 173 - 174." type="journal article" year="1900">Cockerell, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName id="D19366AAFFADFF93FBA7F9D8E44EF9C7" authority="(Hall)" authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[1076,1295,1544,1571]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grevilliae" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="24E7C13BFFADFF93FBA7F9D8E583F9C6" box="[1076,1218,1544,1571]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">C. grevilliae</emphasis>
(Hall)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="24E7C13BFFADFF93FA8AF9D8E4DDF9C7" bold="true" box="[1305,1436,1545,1571]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3FD47C40FFADFF93FA8AF9D8E4DDF9C7" box="[1305,1436,1545,1571]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="8EA801ACFFADFF93FF33F9FDE1A4F9A3" box="[160,229,1580,1607]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1998,2022]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,189,1966]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[170,1417,181,1974]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Cryptinglisia. grevilliae (Hall). Adult female. After Hodgson 1967b." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5222979" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5222979/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="D19366AAFFADFF93FF6DF9FCE342F9A3" authority="(Hodgson)" authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="1969" baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" box="[254,515,1580,1607]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pluvialis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="24E7C13BFFADFF93FF6DF9FCE0C0F9A2" box="[254,385,1580,1607]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">C. pluvialis</emphasis>
(Hodgson)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3FD47C40FFADFF93FD9FF9FCE3D1F9A3" box="[524,656,1581,1607]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" rank="species">
<emphasis id="24E7C13BFFADFF93FD9FF9FCE3CBF9A3" bold="true" box="[524,650,1581,1607]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">comb. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation id="8EA801ACFFADFF93FD31F9FDE3A9F9A3" box="[674,744,1580,1607]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1991,2015]" captionTargetBox="[238,1349,192,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-16@9.[238,1349,181,1967]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Cryptinglisia pluvialis (Hodgson). Adult female. After Hodgson 1967b." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5222983" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5222983/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="D19366AAFFADFF93FCB8F9FCE51FF9A3" authority="(Newstead)" authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Newstead" baseAuthorityYear="1917" box="[811,1118,1580,1607]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="theobromae" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="24E7C13BFFADFF93FCB8F9FCE292F9A2" box="[811,979,1580,1607]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">C. theobromae</emphasis>
(Newstead)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="24E7C13BFFADFF93FBF4F9FCE5A8F9A3" bold="true" box="[1127,1257,1581,1607]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3FD47C40FFADFF93FBF4F9FCE5A8F9A3" box="[1127,1257,1581,1607]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="8EA801ACFFADFF93FB68F9FDE403F9A3" box="[1275,1346,1580,1607]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1916,1940]" captionTargetBox="[163,1434,192,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[151,1436,181,1892]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Cryptinglisia theobromae (Newstead). Adult female. After Hodgson 1967b." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5222989" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5222989/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). A full description of 
<taxonomicName id="D19366AAFFADFF93FEA8F980E0FCF98E" authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="1969" baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" box="[315,445,1616,1643]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pluvialis">
<emphasis id="24E7C13BFFADFF93FEA8F980E0FCF98E" box="[315,445,1616,1643]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">C. pluvialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is given by 
<bibRefCitation id="720260D8FFADFF93FDD9F981E245F98F" author="Hodgson, C. J." box="[586,772,1616,1643]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 42" refId="ref11353" refString="Hodgson, C. J. (1969) Notes on Rhodesian Coccidae (Homoptera: Coccoidea): Part III. Arnoldia, Rhodesia, 4, 1 - 42." type="journal article" year="1969">Hodgson (1969)</bibRefCitation>
, while 
<taxonomicName id="D19366AAFFADFF93FCC4F980E2A2F98E" authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[855,995,1616,1643]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grevilliae">
<emphasis id="24E7C13BFFADFF93FCC4F980E2A2F98E" box="[855,995,1616,1643]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">C. grevilliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D19366AAFFADFF93FB88F980E583F98E" authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Newstead" baseAuthorityYear="1917" box="[1051,1218,1616,1643]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Inglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="theobromae">
<emphasis id="24E7C13BFFADFF93FB88F980E583F98E" box="[1051,1218,1616,1643]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">C. theobromae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are fully described in 
<bibRefCitation id="720260D8FFADFF93FF27F9A5E03DF96B" author="Hodgson, C. J." box="[180,380,1652,1679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref11311" refString="Hodgson, C. J. (1967 b) A revision of the species of Inglisia Maskell (Homoptera: Coccoidea) recorded from the Ethiopian region. Arnoldia, Rhodesia, 3 (23), 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1967">Hodgson (1967b)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="162C1D29FFADFF93FF54F948E46FF932" blockId="6.[151,1437,1436,1751]" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">
It would appear that 
<taxonomicName id="D19366AAFFADFF93FE3CF949E302F956" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1900" box="[431,579,1688,1714]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Cryptinglisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="24E7C13BFFADFF93FE3CF949E302F956" box="[431,579,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">Cryptinglisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has two centres of population, Central and South America and 
<collectingCountry id="6E845DB9FFADFF93FA94F949E4D8F956" box="[1287,1433,1688,1714]" name="South Africa" pageId="6" pageNumber="63">South Africa</collectingCountry>
. There do not appear to be any clear morphological characters separating these 11 species into subgroups.
</paragraph>
